<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Ok looking through the spells and the possible combination of specialization you can have, is it the developers that say you should do 2/3 spec?<P>I mean, you could have 30 Body, 34 Mind, and 29 Matter and basically have a large arsenal of spells at your disposal for different occasions.  Would this seriously gimp you?  <P>I know some have said that spec level effects your resist rate and some have said it doesn't.  From what I have seen it is the level of the creature not your spec level. I get more fails trying to mez purple creature than I do yellow or blue.  Of course it COULD be the level of the creature compared to your spec level, but I am not sure the best way to test that.  Hopefully we'll find out soon  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I am seriously contemplating the 30/34/29 (Body/Mind/Matter) since I have seen first hand what debuffs do.<P>--------------------<P>Malachai Mindbender<BR>Enigmatic of Avalon - Guinivere<BR>Sanguis Societat<BR>http://www.farrout.net/sanguis/memberlist.asp?memberID=8
</FONT>
