<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
The developers have always said that 2/3 spec is acceptable and will give enjoyable results. That's about it.<P>Now, we beta sorcerer players have kind of found out over time that 2/3 is OK but higher is better. That is, until the law of diminishing returns kicks in. I myself found this to be about 90% spec. More than this seems to have no effect. 2/3 is definitely weaker than 90% but in the long run will it make a significant difference? Most feel it won't if you can accept a resist now and again. If you absolutely cannot tolerate a resist ever, you need to go as close to 100% spec as you can get.<P>As to the resist/level/spec relationship, I think its a combo of both. It depends not only on the con of the target in relation to you the caster but to your spec level as well. Both ratios get thrown into the mix so "maximizing" only one won't get the job done.<P>--------------------<P>Nemus Imzadi <BR>Saracen Sorcerer <BR>Knight of Virtue<BR>Champions of Virtue, Bedevere <BR>www.championsofvirtue.com
</FONT>
